modules.description: Provides binary serialization and deserialization operations for a parameterized type, including size calculation, writing, and reading functions tailored to the type's structure. Supports conversion to and from S-expressions and enables transformation of elements within the type via a mapping function. Works with polymorphic container types that wrap a single value.

Encapsulates binary I/O and transformation capabilities for parameterized types, enabling efficient serialization, deserialization, and size computation. Supports S-expression conversion and element-wise mapping, operating on polymorphic containers that wrap a single value. Allows reading and writing of structured data while preserving type-specific transformations. For example, it can serialize a list of integers or convert a wrapped string to uppercase during traversal.

Provides functions to reverse the order of elements in a list and to store the reversed result in a separate data structure. Operates on lists and custom reversed list types with optimized traversal and memory management. Used to efficiently generate and persist reversed sequences for data processing pipelines.

Provides binary I/O and transformation for polymorphic containers, supporting serialization, deserialization, and size calculation. Operates on wrapped values with element-wise mapping and S-expression conversion. Can serialize a list of integers or transform a wrapped string to uppercase. Offers efficient handling of structured data with type-specific operations.
